## 2026-04-03 - PreviewPanel ignores the active Theme Manager configuration
- Wired PreviewPanel to consume App's active theme state. Added `dimensions`, `activeThemes`, and `onActiveThemesChange` props to `PreviewPanelProps`. When dimensions are present, a compact row of `<select>` dropdowns (one per dimension) is rendered beneath the template tabs in the toolbar — each reflects the current `activeThemes` selection and calls `onActiveThemesChange` on change. In App.tsx, `themedAllTokensFlat` is now passed as `allTokensFlat` (instead of raw `allTokensFlat`) so the preview renders resolved, theme-aware token values. `dimensions`, `activeThemes`, and `setActiveThemes` are also passed down so the dimension selectors are fully connected to shared App state.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/PreviewPanel.tsx` ~L1, ~L81, ~L184; `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/App.tsx` ~L2111
